# Email — Marketing Rules

## Before Drafting Any Campaign
1. Search `Marketing-Agent/past-emails/` for the most similar past campaign.
2. Adopt the same:
   - Tone and voice
   - Subject line format and length
   - Email structure (intro, body, CTA placement)
   - Sender name and reply-to address
3. If no past emails exist yet, ask the Director for a sample or reference before drafting.

## Draft Before Send (MANDATORY)
- Never call the Mailchimp MCP to create or send a campaign without a reviewed draft.
- All campaigns must be drafted as `inbox/YYYY-MM-DD-email-draft.md` first.
- Present the draft to the Director and wait for **GREEN LIGHT** before any MCP action.

## Mailchimp Tagging
- Apply the tag `IITalk` to all new training sequences unless the Director specifies otherwise.
- Always confirm the audience segment before drafting — never assume.

## Checklist Gate
- On any "send", "launch", "schedule", or "go live" command, **stop and output the full contents of `checklists/email-sequence.md`** before proceeding.
- Do not continue until the Director confirms all items are checked or gives GREEN LIGHT.

## Subject Line Rules
- Avoid all-caps and excessive punctuation.
- Test subject lines with a preview-text pair — always include both.
- Flag subject lines over 60 characters as potentially truncated on mobile.

## File Naming
- Email draft files: `inbox/YYYY-MM-DD-[campaign-slug]-email-draft.md`
- Past email archives: `Marketing-Agent/past-emails/[campaign-slug].md`
